{
  "doc_id": "32183",
  "text": "GLUT6 was further found to be among the most upregulated genes in different tumor cell lines, like chronic lymphocytic leukemia [CITATION_1] and malignant endometrium [CITATION_2] . Abolishing of GLUT6 expression inhibited glycolysis and survival of endometrial cancer cells [CITATION_3] . GLUT6 was also upregulated in LPS (lipopolysaccharide) stimulated macrophages in an NF-kB (Nuclear factor kappa B) dependent way. In this study, GLUT6 was demonstrated to localize to lysosomal membranes [CITATION_4] . Although LPS-stimulated macrophages exhibit a high level of GLUT6 induction, suppression of GLUT6 expression did not alter the function of this cell line [CITATION_5] . GLUT6 knockout mouse was also developed but did not show significant changes in whole-body physiology [CITATION_6] .",
